gotetris: Tetris Written in Go
==============================

This is a console-based version of Tetris written in Go.

Working on the Code
-------------------

See: https://golang.org/doc/code.html

Setup your Go workspace:

	mkdir -p gotetris/src/github.com/jjinux/gotetris
	echo "See src/github.com/jjinux/gotetris/README." > gotetris/README

	# Do this each time to work on the code.
	cd gotetris
	export GOPATH=`pwd`
	export PATH=$PATH:$GOPATH/bin

	# Install dependencies.
	go get -u github.com/nsf/termbox-go

Build:

	go install github.com/jjinux/gotetris

Execute:

	gotetris

Credits
-------

It's built on top of the https://github.com/nsf/termbox-go library.

This code was inspired by Alexei Kourbatov (http://www.javascripter.net) as
well as my port of Tetris to Dart (http://code.google.com/p/tetris-in-dart/).
